The party's national executive committee (NEC) has briefed the media about its weekend meeting. JOHANNESBURG - The African National Congress (ANC) national executive committee (NEC) is briefing the media about its weekend meeting.WATCH: ANC NEC briefingThe briefing just hours after the Presidency confirmed that President Jacob Zuma has instructed the Minister of Finance Pravin Gordhan and Deputy Minister Mcebisi Jonas to cancel the international investment promotion roadshow to the United Kingdom and the United States and return to South Africa immediately.While the exact reasons for his sudden return are unclear, it has led to fresh speculation that there may be a Cabinet reshuffle.